      "description": "Offering a driver-focused 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six with VarioCam Plus, delivering a linear power band and distinct boxer resonance. This example retains its crisp G96 six-speed manual transaxle and a well-sorted chassis with MacPherson struts and multi-link rear geometry. Recent service includes an inspected IMS bearing and updated rear main seal, ensuring the mechanical longevity of the high-revving powerplant. The four-piston Brembo monoblock calipers provide exceptional thermal management and firm pedal feel. Cosmetically honest with a clean undercarriage, this 911 represents a balanced intersection of analog feedback and modern reliability.",
